org.jvoicexml.xml.vxml
Class Vxml

java.lang.Object
  org.jvoicexml.xml.AbstractXmlNode
      org.jvoicexml.xml.vxml.Vxml
All Implemented Interfaces:
VoiceXmlNode, XmlNode, XmlWritable, Node
public final class Vxml
extends AbstractXmlNode

A VoiceXML document is primiarily composed of top-level elements called dialogs. There are two types of dialogs: forms and menus. A document may also have <meta> and <metadata> elements, <var> and <script> elements, <catch> elements, <property> elements and <link> elements.

ATTRIBUTE_XML_BASE

public static final String ATTRIBUTE_XML_BASE
The base URI for this document as defined in XML Base, J. Marsh, editor, W3C Recommendation, June 2001. As in HTML 4.01 Specification, Dave Ragget et. al. W3C Recommendation, December 1999, a URI which all relative references within the docment take as their base.
